d":"Schotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Schotland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Schotland"},"en":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"before 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"before 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Scotland, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hadden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from the barony of Hadden, Halden, or Haulden (Roxburghshire), or a variant of   Haldane  .","English: variant of   Haddon  .","Irish (Armagh and Tyrone): though mainly Scottish, this surname is sometimes used as an Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hÉidín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Éidín</i>’ (see   Hayden  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Haldane","meanings":["Scottish: from the Middle English and Older Scots personal name <i>Haldan</i> (Old Norse <i>Halfdanr</i>, <i>Half(f)dan</i>, Anglo-Scandinavian <i>Healfdene</i>, literally ‘half Dane’).","Scottish: variant of   Hadden  .","Scottish: shortened form of the Lanarkshire surname <b>McCalden</b>, probably from <i>Mac Haldan</i> ‘son of <i>Haldan</i>’, with the same meaning as 1 above."]},{"name":"Hayden","meanings":["Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó hÉideáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Éideán</i>’ and <b>Ó hÉidín</b> ‘descendant of <i>Éidín</i>’, personal names apparently from a diminutive of <i>éideadh</i> ‘clothes, armor’. There was also a Norman family bearing the English name (see 2 below), living in County Wexford. Alternative spellings include   Hadden  .","English: habitational name from any of various places called Haydon (Dorset, Wiltshire, Somerset, Gloucestershire), Heydon (Cambridgeshire, Norfolk), or Hayden (Gloucestershire, Oxfordshire). Most of the placenames derive from Old English <i>hēg</i> ‘hay’ or <i>(ge)hæg</i> ‘fence, enclosure’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’, though the Cambridgeshire placename has Old English <i>denu</i> ‘valley’ as the final element.","Jewish: variant of   Heiden  ."]},{"name":"Haddan","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Hadden  ."]},{"name":"Haddon","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places, in Derbyshire, Northamptonshire, Huntingdonshire, and Devon, named with Old English <i>hǣth</i> ‘heathland, heather’ + <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’, or from Haddon in Cambridgeshire, which is probably named from the Old English personal name <i>Headda</i> + <i>dūn</i>.","Scottish: variant of   Hadden  ."]}]},{"name":"Helen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["vernacular form of the name (Greek <i>Hēlēnē</i>) borne in classical legend by a famous beauty, wife of Menelaus, whose seizure by the Trojan prince Paris sparked off the Trojan War. Her name is of uncertain origin; it may be connected with a word meaning ‘ray’ or ‘sunbeam’ compare Greek <i>hēlios</i> ‘sun’. It has sometimes been taken as connected with the Greek word meaning ‘Greek’, <i>Hellēn</i>, but this is doubtful. In the early Christian period the name was borne by the mother of the Emperor Constantine, who is now usually known by the Latin version of her name, <i>Helena</i>. She is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Helen Hadden was born in 1240, in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland, her father, Reverend James Hadden, was 26 and her mother, Beatrix Fraser, was 24. She married John Crawford before 1260, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1304, in her hometown, at the age of 64, and was buried in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland."},"et":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"enne 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"enne 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fi":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"ennen vuotta 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"ennen vuotta 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"fr":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"avant 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"avant 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Écosse","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Écosse","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Helen Hadden est née en 1240, à Kilmartin, Argyll, Écosse, son père, Reverend James Hadden, avait 26 ans et sa mère, Beatrix Fraser, avait 24 ans. Elle a épousé John Crawford avant 1260, à Écosse. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Elle est décédée en 1304, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 64 ans, et a été enterrée à Kilmartin, Argyll, Écosse."},"de":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"vor 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"vor 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Schottland, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland","lifeSummary":"Als Helen Hadden 1240 in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland geboren wurde, war ihr Vater Reverend James Hadden 26 und ihre Mutter Beatrix Fraser 24. Sie hat vor 1260 in Scotland John Crawford geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Sie starb 1304 im Alter von 64 Jahren in ihrem Geburtsort und wurde in Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland begraben."},"ht":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"before 1260","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","before 1240":"before 1240","1240":"1240","1273":"1273","1260":"1260","1308":"1308","Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland":"Kilmartin, Argyll, Scotland","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Argyll and Bute, Scotland":"Argyll and Bute, Ecosse, United Kingdom","Argyll, Scotland":"Argyll, Scotland"},"hu":{"1240–1304":"1240–1304","1245–1308":"1245–1308","1260–1310":"1260–1310","1214–1269":"1214–1269","1216–1273":"1216–1273","1304":"1304","1216":"1216","Bef 1260":"1260 előtt","1269":"1269","1214":"1214","1245":"1245","1310":"1310","befo